cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with image denoising. The use of meta-learning also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) category. The paper also mentions the use of synthetic noise models, which could indicate that it belongs to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. Additionally, the use of transfer learning suggests that it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) category. Finally, the evaluation of the proposed approach on both images and 1-D signals suggests that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) category.
